UNIT 4 â€“ Application of Threat Modelling Techniques
Unit Overview

This unit focused on applying threat modelling using practical tools such as OWASP guidance and the MITRE ATT&CK framework.

Artefacts

Threat model diagram

Workshop activity responses

Reflection

Applying threat models to realistic scenarios demonstrated the gap between theory and practice. Tools such as MITRE ATT&CK provided structured threat intelligence, but I also recognised their limitations when contextual business knowledge is missing. This reinforced the importance of human judgement alongside tooling.

References

MITRE (2023). ATT&CK Framework.
https://attack.mitre.org

OWASP (2021). Threat Modeling Cookbook.
https://owasp.org
